ure 8d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.331125090&amp;id=fig08d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08e" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.331125090/asset/images/125090fig08e.jpeg" height="1264" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8e</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.331125090&amp;id=fig08e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.331125090/asset/images/125090fig09.jpeg" height="1280" width="895" aria-labelledby="fig09" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9</span> The Cabrol procedure. Diagram shows the Cabrol procedure, in which a composite aortic graft and a prosthetic conduit that connects the coronary ostia are anastomosed to the aortic graft. Blood flows (arrows) from the aorta into the right and left coronary limbs and, eventually, the coronary arteries.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.331125090&amp;id=fig09">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.331125090/asset/images/125090fig10a.jpeg" height="1280" width="1278" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.331125090&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class